  synonyms :-
  ==========

  => a synonym is another name or alternative name for a table/view

  => if tablename is lengthy then we can give a simple and short name to the table
       called synonym and after creating synonym instead of using table name we can 
        use synonym name in SELECT / INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE queries.

           CREATE SYNONYM <name> FOR <tabname>

  Granting permission to create synonym :-
  ---------------------------------------------------------

   SYSTEM :-
   -----------------
 
  SQL>GRANT CREATE SYNONYM TO BATCH54 ;

 Ex :- 

 SQL>CREATE SYNONYM E FOR EMP ;

 after creating synonym instead of using table name use synonym name 

  SQL>SELECT * FROM E ;
  SQL>UPDATE E SET COMM=500 WHERE EMPNO=7369;
  
 accessing tables without owner name :-
 ----------------------------------------------------------

